Download Screenflow, or another screencast software if you do not already have one.  Obtain a license for Screenflow from IT here
Write a script (located on Github) using this format:
Your name and title (for the intro title card)
Introduction and video overview 
Introduce the value of the product features and explain what the problem is that it solves. Give an example of a real world case study.
Tell the viewer what all you are going to cover in the video.
Video content 
This is the meat of the content, all the step-by-step processes, etc.
Video wrap-up and adtl resources
A very brief recap about what the viewer has learned, and resources where to find more information or people who can answer additional questions. 
Record your video and audio. 
Talk at consistent speed, be aware of language, avoid saying “um”. Tone is somewhat casual and friendly, but always professional. Try not to use acronyms, which can be exclusive for some learners
Demo and Product Walkthrough videos: record audio and video “live” using Screenflow. Training video: audio/video should be recorded one at a time and synced up in post production for the highest quality.
Audio: Ideally audio is recorded in a webinar room such as Snuffy. If this is not possible, you must use an external microphone (not your built-in laptop microphone). If you do not have one, you can order a headset from IT help desk  by filling out a request form here. It should arrive within a few business days. Demo videos and Product walkthrough videos can be You can record your audio and video “live” using Screenflow, or you can record them one at a time and sync them later. 
Video: Ensure you record your screencast at 1920 pixels x 1080 pixels and that your visuals/text are high contrast and easy to read.
Wrap-up
Export your demo video as an mp4 file (web resolution high) and email it, along with your Screenflow project file and a link to your narration transcript to the Services Portfolio team for editing and upload.
